@NODE WHAT_IS_XTRACE "1.1 What is XTrace ?"
@{b}@{u}1.1 What is XTrace ?@{uu}@{ub}

XTrace is an image processing program, which can convert bitmap
pictures to vector pictures by automatically tracing the original
picture. These vector images are very useful for DTP (DeskTop
Publishing).

Basic DTP knowledge is necessary (technical terms) in order to use
XTrace.

To get the best possible results, pictures can be manipulated in
many forms before and after being traced.

Features of XTrace :

 - change colors
 - digital filters
 - color curves support
 - internal list of about 400 colors with their own names
 - shows the pictures in grayscale, with the possibility to show
   single realcolors
 - histogram displaying, stretching and equalizing
 - get rid of unused colors
 - coalescing of resembling colors
 - conversion between different colortypes (palette, gray, b/w)
 - powerful palette editor
 - scaling
 - border processing
 - thinning
 - edge detection/enhancement
 - change of aspect / DPI

 - 3D rotation
 - noise reduction
 - flip picture
 - *full* transparency support
 - usage of Bézier curves

 - uses Clipboard
 - usage of XPK
 - CyberGraphX/Picasso96 support

 - own compact IFF-file format to save all relevant parameters
 - loads IFF-ILBM files directly, with support for other formats
   using Datatypes
 - export traced images as IFF-DR2D, EPSF, EPSI, EPSB, FIG, 
   Adobe Illustrator, HP-GL
 - export traced images as 3D Navigator Titler Logo for Michiel den Outer's
   NTitler
 - export traced fonts as 3D Navigator Titler Font for Michiel den Outer's
   NTitler
 - export 2D and 3D DXF files (good for usage with raytracers)

 - magnifying, cut, eyedropper functions
 - undo

 - multiple simultanous usage of pictures
 - window cleanup

 - screen- and fontsensitive GUI

 - call AmigaGuideź-Online-Help at any time with the <HELP>-key
 
XTrace is, as far as I know, the only available shareware program, which
converts bitmap pictures to vector pictures.

The unregistered version of XTrace places a "DEMO" (text) in every
traced picture and allow only a maximum size of 8 for the font
loader.
@ENDNODE

@NODE WHERE_DOES_XTRACE_RUN "1.2 Where does XTrace run ?"
@{b}@{u}1.2 Where does XTrace run ?@{uu}@{ub}

XTrace runs on any Amigaź, which requires the following equipment:

 - AmigaOS 3.0
 - 2 MB RAM
 - MC 68000

For better performance of the complexe calculations of XTrace a
MC 68030 with 25 MHz and 5 MB RAM are recommended. A FPU is used if
present, but is not necessary. XTrace can use virtual memory (tested with
VMM).

XTrace requires the following libraries to be present in the LIBS:
directory:
            - reqtools.library
            - iffparse.library
            - xpkmaster.library + compression libraries
            - rexxsyslib.library
            - datatypes.library

These libraries will be installed during installation of XTrace or belongs
to the Amiga OS. The BOOPSI-Gadgets gradientslider.gadget and
colorwheel.gadget are in the SYS:Classes/Gadgets directory which belongs to
the Amiga OS 3.x.

XTrace was successfully tested on these Amigaź systems:

Amigaź          Processor(s)    RAM     OS      Graphic-chips / -board

A2000C          MC68060         65 Mb   3.1     Picasso IV / Picasso96
A2000C          MC68060         35 Mb   3.1     Picasso II / CyberGfx
A3000           MC68030/M68882  16 MB   3.1     TIGA A2410 / EGS driver
A4000           MC68060/PPC604e 50 Mb   3.0     AGA
A4000           MC68060         16 Mb   3.1     Cybervision 2 Mb / CyberGfx
@ENDNODE

