@NODE REGISTER "1.4 Registration"
@{b}@{u}1.4 Registration@{uu}@{ub}

XTrace was released under the concept of "Shareware". It is dis-
tributed as a crippled program. To use the full functionality of
XTrace you have to become a registered user. You will get your
personal @{"keyfile" link XTrace_Appendix.guide/GLOSSARY} with your name, address and ID-Number. This @{"keyfile" link XTrace_Appendix.guide/GLOSSARY}
may @{b}not@{ub} be redistributed or given to third persons !

No person(s) or businesses other than the @{"author" link AUTHOR }
are authorized to accept any registration or distribution fees in
any form whatsoever except as specified by the author.

Exclusively people who have sent UKŁ 15.00, US$ 25.00, DM 30.00 or more
(UKŁ 15.00 and US$ 25.00 because of falling exchange rates and rising bank
fees) to the author will be regarded as registered users. Only these three
currencies will be accepted.

Payment can be made in one of the following ways :

- Transfer UKŁ 15.00, US$ 25.00 or DM 30.00 to @{"my" link AUTHOR } bank
  account Nbr.: 1823660556
  at the Sparkasse Leipzig / Germany bank code 86055592.

- Send @{"me" link AUTHOR } an Eurocheque (or a cheque drawn on a german bank) for the amount
  of DM 30.00. Don't forget the card number. ;-)

- Send @{"me" link AUTHOR } a letter with the money inside.

I require in @{b}every@{ub} case the filled in register form (is enclosed at the
XTrace packet). Please fill it in and send it to @{"me" link AUTHOR}.
This @{b}applies particulary too, if you transfer the fee to my account@{ub}, because
of the banks prints wrong names/adresses at my statements of account sometimes.

If you've access to the Internet, you can even register yourself online. To do
this please use the "Online register form" on my homepage (address see below).

I also want you to tell me the name of the next larger neighbour town, if
you are living in a small town or village. I need this name to accomplish
